						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone on the tank bund near the temple of Yellamma.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya I—(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record mentions <hi rend="bold">[Vi]kramāditya Satyā[śray]a.</hi> It seems to register a certain gift made at the request of <hi rend="bold">Kali-Sinda.</hi></p>						

						<p>The characters in which the record is engraved, belong to about the <hi rend="bold">7th century A.D.</hi> It is interesting to note that a portion of the record is written in Sanskrit and the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the <hi rend="bold">Chālukya</hi> family, usually found only in copper-plate grants, is given here.</p>						

						</summary>
